Omollo on his part clarified that overseeing K’Ogalo's future Caf matches depends on the agreement between the two clubs.“I don’t have a problem being available for the upcoming continental matches again, but that will be possible depending on an agreement between the two clubs. I have a contract with Rangers and I have fully resumed my duties,” said Omollo. Posta Rangers chairman John Tanui says the team's tactician Sammy 'Pamzo' Omollo will not available to oversee Gor Mahia's Caf Champions League first round ties against CR Belouizdad of Algeria.
The 49-year-old guided Gor Mahia to their 4-3 aggregate win against APR of Rwanda in the preliminary round.



