His fate at the club hangs in the balance after Football Kenya Federation President Nick Mwendwa also stated that he is not also qualified to be in the technical bench for Gor Mahia's league assignments.
Omollo on his part clarified that overseeing K’Ogalo's future Caf matches depends on the agreement between the two clubs.
“I don’t have a problem being available for the upcoming continental matches again, but that will be possible depending on an agreement between the two clubs. I have a contract with Rangers and I have fully resumed my duties,” said Omollo.
